Can I abuse dynamic typing? Javascript:<p><pre><code>    function f(n) {
        if (typeof n == &#x27;object&#x27;)
            return -1 * n.val;
        else
            return {val: n};
    }
</code></pre>
The unit test passes, so much be good, right?

Nice, but it doesn&#x27;t work for largest possible signed int value:<p>-( 2147483647 + 1 ) this overflows ( in C/C++  )<p>I guess you could change the part of the function to<p><pre><code>       if n > 0 {

		if n%2 == 0 {
			return n - 1
		}
		return (-n) + 1   //here
	}</code></pre>
